      <h1 class='title'>Assets Recovery Agency</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 17 July 2003 vol 409 c61WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_61ws' title='Col. 61WS &mdash; HC Deb 17 July 2003 vol 409 c61WS' name='column_61ws' href='#column_61ws' rel='bookmark'>61WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0409P0-02565'>
        <a name='S6CV0409P0_20030717_CWS_24'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-caroline-flint' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0409P0_20030717_CWS_24' title='Link to this speech by Ms Caroline Flint' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-caroline-flint" title="Ms Caroline Flint">The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for the Home Department (Caroline Flint)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0409P0-02565">I am pleased to announce that the first annual report of the Assets Recovery Agency will be laid before Parliament on 8 September 2003.</p><p id="S6CV0409P0-02566">The report is the first by the agency and covers the financial year 2002&#x2013;03. The agency became operational on 24 February 2003, and the report covers the setting up of the agency and the first few weeks of its work. The next report will include an assessment of how the agency has carried out its first business plan, which was published on 9 July.</p><p id="S6CV0409P0-02567">The agency is already making use of its powers, and has obtained several orders to freeze suspected criminal assets.</p><p id="S6CV0409P0-02568">The establishment of the agency, with extensive powers to investigate and recover criminal assets, shows the Government's commitment to taking the profit out of crime.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
